{
  "word": "diligent",
  "wordRoot": [
    {
      "title": "<span id=\"#29676\" class=\"scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold flex items-center\"><h1 class=\"inline !mb-1 scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold\">diligent</h1><div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(adj.)</div></span>",
      "html": "<p>\"不断努力以完成所承担的事情\"，14世纪中叶，来自古法语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">diligent</span>（14世纪）和直接源自拉丁语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">diligentem</span>（主格 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">diligens</span>）\"注意的，勤奋的，小心的\"，来自 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">diligere</span> \"挑选，高度重视，尊重，珍视，热爱； 渴望，满足，欣赏\"，最初的意思是\"挑选，选择\"，来自 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">dis-</span> \"分开\"（参见 <a href=\"/cn/word/dis-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of dis- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">dis-</a>) + <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">legere</span> \"选择，收集\"，源自 PIE 词根 <a href=\"/cn/word/*leg-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of *leg- \" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">*leg-</a>（1）\"收集，聚集\"，带有意义的派生词是\"说话（挑选词语）\"。相关词汇： <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">Diligently</span>。</p><ins class=\"adsbygoogle relative inline-block transition-all inline-block h-[250px] w-[300px]\" data-ad-slot=\"4000736339\" data-adtest=\"off\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\"></ins>"
    }
  ],
  "relate": [
    {
      "title": "predilection<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(n.)</div>",
      "html": "<p>\"偏爱某事物的心理倾向\"，1742年，源自法语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">prédilection</i>（16世纪），是由中世纪拉丁语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">praedilectus</i> 的动作名词构成，该词是 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">prediligere</i> 的过去分词，意为“优先选择”，由拉丁语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">prae</i> “在...之前”（见 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of pre- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/pre-\">pre-</a>)和 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">diligere</i> “选择，爱”（见 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of diligent \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/diligent\">diligent</a>）组成。动词 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">predilect</i>（1774）很少使用或已经过时。</p>"
    },
    {
      "title": "dis-<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\"></div>",
      "html": "<p>拉丁语词缀，意为1. “缺乏，不”（如 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of dishonest \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/dishonest\">dishonest</a>）； 2. “相反，做相反的事”（如 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of disallow \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/disallow\">disallow</a>）； 3. “分开，离开”（如 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of discard \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/discard\">discard</a>），源自古法语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">des-</i> 或直接源自拉丁语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">dis-</i>，意为“分开，分离，朝不同方向，比喻为‘不，非’，也表示‘极其，完全’。在大多数有声辅音前，它被同化为 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">dif-</i>，在 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">-f-</i> 前被同化为 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">di-</i>。</p><p>拉丁语前缀来自原始印欧语言的 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">*dis-</i>，意为“分开，分离”（源自古英语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">te-</i>，古撒克逊语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">ti-</i>，古高地德语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">ze-</i>，德语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">zer-</i>）。原始印欧语言的根词是 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">*dwis-</i> 的次生形式，因此与拉丁语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">bis</i> “两次”（最初为 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">*dvis</i>）和 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">duo</i> 有关，表示“两种方式，分开”（因此表示“分开，分离”）。</p><p>在古典拉丁语中， <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">dis-</i> 与 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of de- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/de-\">de-</a> 相似，意思也差不多，但在后期拉丁语中， <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">dis-</i> 成为首选形式，并传入古法语中，成为古法语中形成复合词的形式，越来越具有否定意义（“不”）。在英语中，许多这些词最终被改回了 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">dis-</i>，而在法语中，许多词被改回了 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">de-</i>。通常存在混淆。</p><p>作为英语中的一个活前缀，它反转或否定了它所附着的词。有时，如意大利语中，它被缩减为 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">s-</i>（如 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of spend \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/spend\">spend</a>， <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of splay \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/splay\">splay</a>， <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of sport \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/sport\">sport</a>， <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">sdain</i> 表示 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of disdain \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/disdain\">disdain</a>，以及姓氏 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of Spencer \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/Spencer\">Spencer</a> 和 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">Spence</i>）。</p>"
    },
    {
      "title": "*leg-<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(1)</div>",
      "html": "<p>“收集，聚集”是原始印欧语言词根，派生出“讲话”的意思，指“聚集语言，挑选词汇”。</p><p>它构成或成为以下词汇的一部分： <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of alexia \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/alexia\">alexia</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of analects \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/analects\">analects</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of analogous \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/analogous\">analogous</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of analogue \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/analogue\">analogue</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of analogy \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/analogy\">analogy</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of anthology \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/anthology\">anthology</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of apologetic \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/apologetic\">apologetic</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of apologue \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/apologue\">apologue</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of apology \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/apology\">apology</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of catalogue \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/catalogue\">catalogue</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of coil \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/coil\">coil</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of colleague \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/colleague\">colleague</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of collect \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/collect\">collect</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of college \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/college\">college</a>